# Credits and third-party attribution

When adding or updating **attribution** for people or **bundled third-party code**, use these locations only—do not invent parallel files under `doc/` or scattered README-only notices without also updating the canonical places below.

## AUTHORS (repository root)

- **People:** Keep contributor credits in `AUTHORS` using the existing sections and tone.
- **Libraries and packaged code:** Add a short line under **“Libraries and code segments are included from the following projects:”** (name, optional upstream URL). This is the human-readable index shipped inside the app on the Credits **Authors** tab.

## THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt (repository root)

- **Full license / notice text** required for in-app disclosure (BSD/MIT-style notices, copyright blocks, etc.) belongs in **`THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt` at the repository root**, not under `doc/`.
- Organise by component (markdown headings work in the Credits viewer). Keep UTF-8 valid; prefer markdown links for URLs where helpful.
- **Do not** replace or duplicate the main XCSoar **GPL** text here—that remains `COPYING` on its own Credits tab.

## Build embedding (`build/resource.mk`)

- Gzip-embedded text files for the Credits dialog are listed in **`TEXT_FILES`** in `build/resource.mk`. Any new root-level notice file that must appear in Credits must be added there (today: `AUTHORS`, `COPYING`, `NEWS.txt`, `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt`).
- After changing `TEXT_FILES`, the linker exposes `*_gz` / `*_gz_size` symbols consumed by `dlgCredits.cpp`.

## macOS bundle (`build/osx.mk`)

- If third-party notices must ship as a loose file in the `.app` bundle, mirror the pattern for **`THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt`** (copy target under `APP_RESOURCES`) when touching packaging.

## Credits UI (`src/Dialogs/dlgCredits.cpp`)

- **Order and captions:** New scroll pages must stay consistent with **`add_scroll_page`** order and the **`third_party_page_index` / `license_page_index`** logic (and `titles[]`) so pager captions stay correct.
- **Third-party tab content** is markdown-enabled (`RichTextWidget`); **GPL** (`COPYING`) stays plain text.
- The **Third-party** pager label is intentionally fixed English (not passed through `gettext()`); do not mark it for translation unless the project explicitly changes that policy.

## Checklist for a new bundled dependency

1. Line (and URL if useful) in **`AUTHORS`** under libraries/code segments.
2. If required: section + full notice wording in **`THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt`**.
3. Confirm **`TEXT_FILES`** / **`dlgCredits.cpp`** still match if filenames or page order changes.
